&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Challenge 🧩&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a collaborative &lt;strong&gt;Brand Strategy &amp;amp; Research Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; who excels at uncovering market and consumer insights and translating them into strategic value to support our brand growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will coordinate and analyze brand measurement across all regions, serving as a core pillar for Wallapop&#39;s Brand Strategy. If you believe that research doesn&#39;t end with delivering data, but rather continues into shaping what comes next, this is the perfect opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Depending on the project, you will partner cross-functionally with teams such as Marketing Operations, Creative, UX Research, and Paid Media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do 👇&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute Research:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and oversee both quantitative research (e.g., market research, brand tracking, NPS) and qualitative studies (e.g., focus groups), collaborating with external partners or managing them in-house to deliver high-quality projects on time and within budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Synthesize Insights:&lt;/strong&gt; Analyze and organize macro data points, communicating them clearly to act as a central hub for identifying new opportunities and solving problems for Wallapop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the development of our Brand Strategy by providing key insights and strategic thinking. Act as a direct stakeholder for specific projects—from audience definition to building creative briefings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Empower Teams:&lt;/strong&gt; Interpret and present findings to marketing stakeholders, transforming complex data into clear, actionable strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with the UX team on cross-category projects to help create a centralized knowledge base that fuels both the marketing and product teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitor the Market:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate with the Media team to track and analyze competitor activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven experience leading and executing quantitative market research projects end-to-end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic &amp;amp; Analytical Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to look at data critically, connect disparate data points, and form a clear strategic point of view.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong coordination and organizational skills, with a proven ability to manage multiple moving parts and adapt to a dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Literacy:&lt;/strong&gt; Proficiency in using spreadsheet tools (like Excel or Google Sheets) for professional data analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Professional verbal and written communication skills in both &lt;strong&gt;English and Spanish&lt;/strong&gt;, with the interpersonal skills needed to influence cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem-Solving &amp;amp; Agility:&lt;/strong&gt; A proactive, resourceful approach to challenges with a desire to continuously learn, grow, and adapt to shifting priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
